Are You Asking For A Break On Mortgage, Rent Or Other Bills?
Enlarge this image Katherine Du/NPR Katherine Du/NPRBanks are being ordered to allow people hurt financially in the coronavirus pandemic to skip mortgage payments.
Some lenders are doing this for auto loans, credit cards and small business loans with no negative impact on people's credit scores.
If you're asking for this kind of help, NPR wants to hear from you.
